It’s been just over one year since the disaster and residents say despite the promises made they’ve received no help. The Eastern Cape Cooperative Governance Department says it's looking into the matter. eTV's Mbasa Khwaza has more. Courtesy #DStv403 MTHATHA - The R41-million meant to help Eastern Cape residents rebuild their lives seems to have been used to pay the salaries of municipal workers. The disaster relief funds were intended to be used to rebuild hundreds of homes destroyed by a storm in the OR Tambo District Municipality in November last year. READ: Eastern Cape Floods | Mop-up operations underway But residents are still waiting for proper housing. The Eastern Cape Cooperative Governance Department says it's looking into the matter. * Mbasa Khwaza reports.